</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E254F15FCB4389DFA8BFB29" blockId="17.[820,1435,1222,1275]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E254F15FCB4389DFC05FB09" box="[820,945,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin noun for point, referring to the pointed apex of the ovipositor in lateral view.
</paragraph>
